### 6. CONVERSATION ADDITION LOGIC

**File:** `manager.ts` lines 2603-2655

```typescript
private addConversationToFolder(folderId: string, dragData: DragData): void {
  if (!this.data.folderContents[folderId]) {
    this.data.folderContents[folderId] = [];
  }

  // Check if already exists
  const exists = this.data.folderContents[folderId].some(
    (c) => c.conversationId === dragData.conversationId,
  );
  if (exists) return;

  // Create ConversationReference
  const conv: ConversationReference = {
    conversationId: dragData.conversationId!,
    title: dragData.title,
    url: dragData.url!,
    addedAt: Date.now(),
    isGem: dragData.isGem,
    gemId: dragData.gemId,
    sortIndex: maxSortIndex + 1,
  };

  this.data.folderContents[folderId].push(conv);

  // If dragged from another folder, remove from source
  if (dragData.sourceFolderId && dragData.sourceFolderId !== folderId) {
    this.removeConversationFromFolder(dragData.sourceFolderId, dragData.conversationId!);
    return;  // removeConversationFromFolder calls saveData() & refresh()
  }

  this.saveData();
  this.refresh();
}
```

**Multi-select version** (`manager.ts` lines 2658-2723):
- Deduplicates conversation IDs
- Maintains sort indices
- Removes from source folder(s) if moving
- Handles cross-folder selections

---

### 7. FOLDER NESTING RULES

**Key constraint:** Folders can have **2 levels max** (parent + children):
- Root folder (parentId = null)
- Folder with children (parentId = null, has children)
- Subfolder (parentId = some folder ID, cannot have children)

**Dragging constraint** (`manager.ts` line 1276-1277):
```typescript
private canFolderBeDragged(folderId: string): boolean {
  return !this.data.folders.some((f) => f.parentId === folderId);  // No subfolders
}
```

This means:
- ✅ Empty folders can be dragged
- ✅ Folders with children CANNOT be dragged (prevents nesting deeper than 2 levels)

---

### 8. MULTI-SELECT MECHANISM

**Activation:** Long-press (500ms+) on a conversation element

**File:** `manager.ts` lines 1401-1416

```typescript
const handleMouseDown = (e: MouseEvent) => {
  if (e.button !== 0) return;  // Left button only
  longPressTriggered = false;

  const conversationId = this.extractConversationId(element);

  longPressTimeoutId = window.setTimeout(() => {
    longPressTriggered = true;
