### 10. EVENT PROPAGATION STRATEGY

**Critical pattern:** `e.stopPropagation()` is used extensively to prevent bubbling

Example hierarchy problem:
```
Root Drop Zone (list)
  ├── Folder 1 (header + content area)
  │   └── Conversation 1
  └── Folder 2
```

Without `stopPropagation()`:
- Drop on Folder 1 would ALSO trigger Root Zone handler
- Would add conversation to BOTH Folder 1 AND root

**Solution:** Each drop handler calls `e.stopPropagation()` to stop bubbling up

---

### 11. KNOWN EDGE CASES & SOLUTIONS

| Issue | Location | Solution |
|-------|----------|----------|
| Dragleave fires on child elements | manager.ts line 1124 | Use coordinate check (setupRootDropZone) or counter (aistudio.ts) |
| Folder can be dragged onto itself | manager.ts line 2735 | Check: `if (draggedFolderId === targetFolderId) return` |
| Folder dragged onto descendant | manager.ts line 2741 | Check: `if (this.isFolderDescendant(...)) return` |
| Folders with children can be nested infinitely | manager.ts line 1276 | Block dragging: `canFolderBeDragged()` returns false if folder has subfolders |
| Duplicate conversations in folder | manager.ts line 2617 | Check: `const exists = this.data.folderContents[folderId].some(...)` |
| Opacity not restored on failed drag | manager.ts line 1139 | Pre-cleanup in drop handler before processing |
| Multi-select from different folders | manager.ts line 1080 | Store sourceFolderId in dragData (line 959) |

---

### 12. SUMMARY TABLE: WHAT CAN DROP WHERE

| Drag Source | Drop Target | Supported? | Handler |
|------------|------------|-----------|---------|
| Conversation (native) | Folder header | ✅ Yes | `setupDropZone()` |
| Conversation (native) | Folder content area | ✅ Yes | `setupDropZone()` |
| Conversation (native) | Root zone | ✅ Yes | `setupRootDropZone()` |
| Conversation (native) | Between conversations | ✅ Yes (reorder) | `setupConversationReorderZone()` |
| Multiple conversations | Any folder | ✅ Yes | `addConversationsToFolder()` |
| Folder (no children) | Another folder | ✅ Yes | `addFolderToFolder()` |
| Folder (no children) | Root zone | ✅ Yes | `moveFolderToRoot()` |
| Folder (with children) | Any drop target | ❌ No | `canFolderBeDragged()` blocks it |

